.TH "wear_leveling_worker" 9 "wear_leveling_worker" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wear_leveling_worker \- wear-leveling worker function.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" wear_leveling_worker
.BI "(struct ubi_device *ubi "  ","
.BI "struct ubi_work *wrk "  ","
.BI "int shutdown "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ubi" 12
UBI device description object
.IP "wrk" 12
the work object
.IP "shutdown" 12
non-zero if the worker has to free memory and exit
because the WL-subsystem is shutting down
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function copies a more worn out physical eraseblock to a less worn out
one. Returns zero in case of success and a negative error code in case of
failure.
